all of these pizzas on time?

145
00:07:02,881 --> 00:07:03,971
Tell me that!

146
00:07:09,346 --> 00:07:12,556
‐ Excuse me, please,
please, please stop.

147
00:07:12,641 --> 00:07:13,681
Stop, will you, please?

148
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:16,557
‐ You’re not gonna
get anywhere that way.

149
00:07:16,645 --> 00:07:18,865
We’re quickly
running out of time,

150
00:07:18,939 --> 00:07:22,019
we can’t deliver all our pizzas
with an ordinary air car.

151
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:23,608
I’ll help you out here.

152
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:32,540
(horn blaring)

153
00:07:36,081 --> 00:07:37,461
‐ Hey, what’s the
matter, Ranpha?

154
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:38,960
Argh!

155
00:07:39,084 --> 00:07:40,714
‐ No one ever seems to be here,

156
00:07:40,794 --> 00:07:43,054
so we thought we’d
let ourselves in.

157
00:07:43,129 --> 00:07:44,709
You don’t pay up and
you’re hanging around

158
00:07:44,798 --> 00:07:46,878
with your girl here
like it’s nothing?

159
00:07:46,967 --> 00:07:48,587
You’ve sure got nerve.

160
00:07:48,677 --> 00:07:50,717
‐ It’s not like
he’s my boyfriend,

161
00:07:50,804 --> 00:07:52,604
we haven’t even
done anything yet.

162
00:07:52,681 --> 00:07:53,931
‐ Are you lovesick or what?

163
00:07:54,015 --> 00:07:56,385
Have you ever seen
one of these before?

164
00:07:56,476 --> 00:07:57,936
‐ Stop it!

165
00:07:58,019 --> 00:08:00,559
This has nothing to do with
her, so leave her out of it!

166
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:03,067
‐ Ah, you’re so sweet.

167
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:04,229
‐ I’ll use this.
‐ Huh?

168
00:08:04,317 --> 00:08:05,687
‐ Huh?

169
00:08:05,819 --> 00:08:06,899
(screaming)

170
00:08:06,987 --> 00:08:09,657
‐ If you’re gonna kill
us, take me first.

171
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:12,869
‐ Hey, you, what are you doing?

172
00:08:12,993 --> 00:08:14,453
Trying to kill yourself?

173
00:08:14,536 --> 00:08:15,746
‐ Oh, Mint.

174
00:08:15,829 --> 00:08:17,329
‐ What are you pulling here?

175
00:08:17,414 --> 00:08:18,964
Are you looking for
trouble or what?

176
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,710
Well?
‐ Well?

177
00:08:20,834 --> 00:08:23,214
‐ I just tripped and
fell, that’s all.

178
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:24,836
‐ You tripped and fell?

179
00:08:24,963 --> 00:08:27,013
‐ So tell me, why are
you just lying there

180
00:08:27,132 --> 00:08:30,512
with your eyes closed like
you’re praying, you idiot?

181
00:08:30,635 --> 00:08:31,885
‐ All our creditors

182
00:08:32,012 --> 00:08:34,182
have been constantly
threatening us with violence,

183
00:08:35,098 --> 00:08:36,968
we’ve suffered so much

184
00:08:37,058 --> 00:08:39,978
that well, my sister
and I thought we’d just.

185
00:08:41,271 --> 00:08:42,361
‐ Easy, sis.

186
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:45,530
‐ Well, what about
your Mom and Dad, huh?

187
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:48,028
(light melancholic music)

188
00:08:48,153 --> 00:08:51,363
‐ Some 10 years ago,
they passed away.

189
00:08:51,448 --> 00:08:54,238
Ever since then, we’ve
been making pizza.

190
00:08:54,367 --> 00:08:56,447
(crying)

191
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:59,040
‐ The boss!
‐ The boss!

192
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:01,750
(crying)

193
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:04,045
I know, I know how you feel.

194
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:07,210
‐ We’re really thankful
for your compassion.

195
00:09:07,338 --> 00:09:09,218
Would you help us
deliver our pizzas?

196
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,680
(crying)

197
00:09:12,761 --> 00:09:15,891
I know that we’ll
be interrupting your
normal work schedule,

198
00:09:16,014 --> 00:09:18,894
so I promise that
we’ll repay you.

199
00:09:19,017 --> 00:09:20,387
Will this be alright?

200
00:09:21,770 --> 00:09:24,440
And then there’s the problem
of our living expenses,

201
00:09:24,564 --> 00:09:27,114
there’s the power bill
and the water bill,

202
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:28,573
we’ll also need
some new clothes,

203
00:09:28,693 --> 00:09:31,823
we’ve been wearing what we have
on for five years, you know

204
00:09:31,905 --> 00:09:33,865
and it would be nice
to eat something

205
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:35,578
other than pizza
once in a while,

206
00:09:35,658 --> 00:09:38,578
when was the last
time we had cake?

207
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:39,951
I can’t even remember

208
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:43,170
and we’d really like a
proper grave for our parents.

209
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:44,749
‐ A grave!
(crying)

210
00:09:44,834 --> 00:09:47,174
‐ and we need to fix
the hole in the roof.

211
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:50,053
‐ Hey, boss, these kids
are hurting so much,

212
00:09:50,131 --> 00:09:52,301
